																		Author Notes
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/blibby-blobfish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2945030); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2945030&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204697" alt="Blibby_Blobfish" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2945030)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/blibby-blobfish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2945030); return false;" >Blibby_Blobfish</a></span> <span class="odate time_1494186482 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 May 2017 19:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2813682">
									

<p>First jab at a manual-style document. I've made efforts to account for new members, by linking to all references so hopefully no inexperienced readers go &quot;what the hell is that?&quot;.</p>
<p>This is in no way meant to be a hub, or a canon for people to follow. It conflicts many headcanons of other users. It's my head - incorporating only my ideas - and it's up to you to accept it or not.</p>
<p>No, this is not supposed to be a guide.</p>
<p>It's something I enjoyed writing and I hope you enjoy it too.</p>
<p>Thanks to Banana Republic, tretter, MrWrong, Otmas, Zyn, Weryllium, and a huge thanks to Agent MacLeod for critics and reviews.</p>
<p>If you want me to link your SCP/tale to this, just give me the link, tell me why and where to put it.</p>
<p>EDIT: (5th Sept. 2018) Massive re-write of 04 command, alert code system, lockdown classifications and ARIs.</p>
<p>EDIT EDIT: (8th Sept.) Re-organisation of categories and huge overhaul of aesthetics. Love to hear your opinions on whether it looks better/cleaner this way.</p>

							</div>

								
