														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2816709">
									

<p>(Summoned by PM<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-737710-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-737710-1')">1</a></sup>)This is quality and quantity work, but it goes on too long, and doesn't fulfill any need for me.</p>
<p>Does this entertain me? No, it's too dense and lacks a narrative structure. You could address that by changing it to an orientation tale.</p>
<p>Is it logical in-universe? Not really. It starts as how to handle a lockdown, then veers off into a list of MTFs, while mentioning some material the foundation doesn't trust recruits with<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-737710-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-737710-2')">2</a></sup>. You could address this by separating it into two works: A new employee's guide to Lockdowns, and a senior review of active MTFs.</p>
<p>Is it helpful to new readers of the wiki? Maybe. A little info on a lot of subjects would not interest me as a new reader.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-737710-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-737710-1')">1</a>. To my complete and happy surprise</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-737710-2"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-737710-2')">2</a>. The origin of the CI, for instance</div>
</div>

